oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Panoramic photograph of USS Birmingham and portrait of Eddie Moran
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This panoramic photograph of USS Birmingham was taken in 1919. The crew is shown standing on the deck of this Chester class scout cruiser. The small oval framed photograph of Eddie Moran set into the left matt margin of the ship's image is probably his recruitment photograph as the talley on his cap has "TRAINING" on it. Moran lived in Nashville after the World War, 1914-1918, and later moved to N. J. The USS Birmingham was the first ship to launch an airplane in 1910. She was decommissioned in 1923.
